
Since 1925, Atlanta businesses have donated millions of dollars to Forward Atlanta, corporate Atlanta's war chest that helped in the bid for the 1996 Olympics and continues to launch initiatives to improve the region's quality of life. The current five-year Forward Atlanta campaign underscores its broad corporate support: 182 companies, dozens of them with headquarters outside Georgia and the United States, have contributed $23 million. But one major Atlanta company &mdash; which was a contributor in the two previous campaigns &mdash; is missing from the list of donors. 

